      sections: [
        {
          id: "end-of-pre-season",
          title: "End of Pre-Season",
          body: [
            "Once the Pre-Season ends, based on the countdown available in the Season tile, your server will start the actual Season 1.",
            "Head over to the Season 1 – The Crimson Plague page to continue the exploration of this new adventure."
          ],
          image: {
            alt: "RA virus molecule",
            src: new URL("../../mirror/www.lastwartutorial.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/virus-molecule.png", import.meta.url).href
          }
        },
        {
          id: "1-what-is-the-last-war-season-1-pre-season",
          title: "1. What is the Last War Season 1 Pre-Season?",
          body: [
            "Answer: Season 1 Pre-Season is a 2‑week setup phase before The Crimson Plague. You preview rewards, rules, warzone groupings and events like Season Boost, Season Preview and Capitol Conquest so your alliance can plan territory and war strategy early.",
            "Learn more about the Season 1 Pre-Season overview"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "2-what-unlocks-in-last-war-first-pre-season-week",
          title: "2. What unlocks in Last War first Pre-Season week?",
          body: [
            "Answer: In week 1 you get the Season 1 timeline tile, Season Boost and Season Preview. From there you can check story, warzone groupings, Week 1 rules and a rewards preview so you know which objectives and alliances to prepare around immediately.",
            "See First Pre-Season Week details"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "3-how-do-i-use-the-season-1-timeline-tile",
          title: "3. How do I use the Season 1 timeline tile?",
          body: [
            "Answer: Open the Season 1 main timeline tile to see four key areas: story info, warzone grouping, Week 1 rules and a Season 1 rewards preview. Use grouping to scout future opponents and rules plus rewards to plan which events to push hardest.",
            "Learn more about the Season 1 main timeline tile"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "4-how-does-the-last-war-season-boost-work",
          title: "4. How does the Last War Season Boost work?",
          body: [
            "Answer: Season Boost shows all global bonuses active in Season 1. During Pre‑Season you can preview troop and economy boosts; hero boosts appear later, only when their hero events run. Check it before spending to time upgrades and training with buffs.",
            "Learn more about Season Boost bonuses"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "5-what-does-the-last-war-season-preview-reveal",
          title: "5. What does the Last War Season Preview reveal?",
          body: [
            "Answer: Season Preview first shows a teaser, then each day reveals more details once that day’s goal is cleared. As you progress, you uncover event info and can claim one‑time chest rewards, helping you understand which activities will matter most.",
            "See Season Preview rewards and details"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "6-what-changes-in-the-second-pre-season-week",
          title: "6. What changes in the second Pre-Season week?",
          body: [
            "Answer: In week 2, Season Preview fully unlocks and you start revealing all remaining info and rewards by clearing daily objectives. This week leads directly into Capitol Conquest on Day 6, so use it to finalize troop, shield and alliance war prep.",
            "Learn more about the Second Pre-Season Week"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "7-how-does-capitol-conquest-work-in-last-war",
          title: "7. How does Capitol Conquest work in Last War?",
          body: [
            "Answer: Capitol Conquest happens on Day 6 of Pre‑Season week 2. Any alliance can join without adjacent land. The battle lasts up to 4 hours; the first to 100% capture, or the highest progress when time ends, wins and its leader becomes President.",
            "See Capitol Conquest event details"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "8-how-can-my-alliance-join-capitol-conquest",
          title: "8. How can my alliance join Capitol Conquest?",
          body: [
            "Answer: During Pre‑Season you don’t need territory next to the Capitol. Just move squads into the contaminated area when the event opens. Be ready to lose your shield on first attack, then coordinate up to 100 defending squads once you garrison it.",
            "Learn more about Capitol Conquest participation rules"
          ],
          image: null
        },
        {
          id: "9-how-to-farm-honor-points-in-capitol-conquest",
          title: "9. How to farm Honor Points in Capitol Conquest?",
          body: [
            "Answer: To maximize Honor Points, keep squads fighting inside the mud area while the event is active. Attacking the Capitol and battling other squads both count; kills and your own troop losses add Honor. Points stop once the stage says “Outcome settled”.",
            "See Honor Point optimization tips for Capitol Conquest"
          ],
          image: null
        }
      ]
